deck: A journalist investigates a creepy town where all residents have lost their memories. By Ben McCool and Nikki Cook.
description: One day, the residents of Lowesille lost their memory; who they were, where they were, and what happened to them. It is one of those strange mysteries believed by skeptics to be an elaborate revenue generating hoax. Trent MacGowan is a journalist planning to spend a week at the town to uncover the truth. Upon arrival, Trent is met with hostility that seems to go beyond the normal hatred of strangers. Several of them seem outright crazy. When one of the residents uncovers a mass grave, it becomes evident there's much more to the story, and one townsperson remembers everything.
name: Memoir

description: Comedic take on the Steampunk series putting US Government Officials in the forefront. Sarah Palin stars in this satirical story about one woman wanting to convert the world from Oil and Nuclear power to steam, only to have an attempt made at her life, leaving her partially rebuilt using parts from a steam mech. Obama (alias "Robama") brings them all together to fight the greater evil, Nuke Oil run by the corrupted Al Gore.
name: Steampunk Palin

description:
Zenescope Presents a new ongoing series that promises to be one of the hottest independent titles of the year. After the milestone events of Grimm Fairy Tales #50 creatures from the realm of Myst have escaped into our world. Captured by the evil Baba Yaga for her sinister plans they are about to cause major havoc on earth. Written by Raven Gregory (Zenescopes Wonderland trilogy) this first arc revisits the characters and story from the very first issue of Grimm Fairy Tales Little Red Riding Hood. Brittany, our hero from issue #1 is back, working in a treatment center for adolescents. Little does she know that something from another realm has caught her scent and will stop at nothing to find and destroy her before her true purpose is revealed.

The series continues with the same format. Characters from the original series are introduced here in story arcs. Additionally the main heroine of this series is Samantha Darren who works against the manipulations of the dark forces aligned against her. In some story arcs she is featured working towards that goal (such as in the Gathering and the Summoning.)

Collected Editions

  • Grimm Fairy Tales: Myths & Legends vol. 1 (#1-5)
  • Grimm Fairy Tales: Myths & Legends vol. 2 (#8-11)
  • Grimm Fairy Tales: Myths & Legends vol. 3 (#12-15)
  • Grimm Fairy Tales: Myths & Legends vol. 4 (#18-21)
  • Grimm Fairy Tales: Myths & Legends vol. 5 (#16-17 & 22-25)
name: Grimm Fairy Tales: Myths & Legends

description:
On the eve of the festival celebrating the return of the original Superman from his long exile in the heart of the sun, the member of Justice Legion A the mightiest heroes of the years 85,271 come back in time to invite the greatest heroes of the 20 Century the Justice League of America to travel to the future and take part in the celebration.

But both teams fall victim to a plot millennia in the making. Stranded in the future, the JLA are hunted as dangerous renegades. Meanwhile, their counterparts in the Justice Legion A must find a cure for a deadly virus they have unwittingly brought into their past our present and deal with a traitor in their midst.

Collects DC One Million #1-4, JLA and Starman #1,000,000 and portions of the tie-in issues of Detective Comics, Green Lantern, Resurrection Man, and Superman: The Man of Tomorrow.
name: JLA: One Million
